comments.body:
@esomir Can you re-check whether the created docker-archive is encrypted, please? In my testing, the config is unencrypted, but the layers are neither valid tar files nor valid `gzip`; it seems skopeo does encrypt the layers, it “only” discards the encryptions annotations that would allow decrypting them.

Is it possible that your Docker daemon already had the same `nginx` image present locally, so `docker load` only read the (unencrypted) config and determined that they layer files are not necessary to read, so it did not notice that they are unreadable?

It would be best to test this with an empty Docker image store.
